  "prompt": "How can I choose between my dad and my mom?",
  "response": "It's generally not healthy or beneficial to \"choose\" between your parents. Family dynamics can be complex, and being forced to take sides can cause emotional stress. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. If there are serious issues like abuse or conflict:\n- Seek support from a counselor or trusted adult\n- Prioritize your own well-being and safety\n- Try to maintain healthy boundaries\n\n2. If the conflict is less severe:\n- Listen to both perspectives\n- Avoid taking sides\n- Communicate openly and respectfully\n- Try to help them communicate with each other\n\n3. Maintain relationships with both parents if possible:\n- Spend time with each of them\n- Show love and respect\n- Don't let their conflicts affect your relationship with them\n\n4. If the situation is very difficult:\n- Consider family therapy\n- Talk to a school counselor\n- Seek guidance from other trusted adults\n\nRemember, you don't have to choose. Both parents are important, and ideally, you should be able to have a relationship with both of them.\n\nWould you like to discuss your specific situation in more detail?",
